Tesla was not born, nor he lived in Croatia at any point. I started the discussion for him to be removed from that list. Until then, I removed the reference.
/* Tesla's own opinion regarding his homeland */
/* Tesla's own opinion regarding his homeland */
Serbo-Croatian language is the term used in Yugoslavia. That term does not belong to Tesla's time. He was a Serb, thus he spoke Serbian language.

[[Yugoslav Wars]] is more generally accepted term, since the term "Croatian war of independence" is only used in Croatia. It also corrects the statement that both house and church have been burned down (see sources in [[Smiljan]]).
